'''''Election''''' is a 2013 Indian [[Cinema of Karnataka|Kannada]] [[Action film|action]] [[Drama film|drama]] film directed by [[Om Prakash Rao]] and produced by [[Ramu (film producer)|Ramu]] under the banner Ramu Enterprises. The film stars [[Malashri]] in the lead role. The supporting cast features [[Pradeep Rawat (actor)|Pradeep Rawat]], [[Dev Gill]], [[Sharath Lohitashwa]], Hanumanthegowda and [[Suchendra Prasad]].
The film was later dubbed in Hindi as
Sher E Jigar in 2018 on WAM.<ref>https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=SaNo3pj9pXQ&t=3098s</ref>

== Cast ==
* [[Malashri]] as Indira
* [[Pradeep Rawat (actor)|Pradeep Rawat]] as Narasimha
* [[Dev Gill]] as Deviprasad
* [[Srinivasa Murthy]]
* [[Sharath Lohitashwa]] as Vishwanath
* Hanumanthegowda as Gangadhara
* [[Suchendra Prasad]] as Ramaswamy
* [[Sadhu Kokila]]
* [[Bullet Prakash]]
* [[Meghana Naidu]] as an item number

== Production ==

=== Filming ===
The filming of ''Election'' began on 8 December 2012 in [[Bangalore]].<ref>{{cite news |title= Malashri is Commissioner |url= http://www.indiaglitz.com/malashri-is-commissioner-kannada-news-89011 |publisher= ''indiaglitz.com |date= 10 December 2012 |accessdate= 30 April 2014}}</ref>

=== Pre-release revenues ===
The satellite rights of the film were sold for {{INRConvert|2.5|c}}.<ref>{{cite news |title= 2.5 crore for Malashree's Election's TV rights |url= http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movies/news-interviews/2-5-crore-for-Malashrees-Elections-TV-rights/articleshow/18861028.cms |newspaper= The Times of India |date= 8 March 2013 |accessdate= 30 April 2014}}</ref>

