== Reception ==
''Election'' received mixed to negative response from critics upon its theatrical release. G. S. Kumar of ''[[The Times of India]]'' gave the film a rating of three out of five and wrote, "Director N Omprakash Rao has done a good job of a story that helps you understand the lifestyle of politicians, how they indulge in goondaism, sex and luring voters with gifts, including money." and praised the role of acting and cinematography in the film.<ref>{{cite news |title= Election review |url= http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/kannada/movie-reviews/Election/movie-review/20247814.cms |newspaper= The Times of India |date= 24 May 2013 |accessdate= 30 April 2014}}</ref>

